# GitHub

## GitHub CLI (`gh`)

Use `gh` as the primary tool for GitHub operations. Prefer `gh` over the web UI for scriptable, reproducible workflows.

### Common Operations

```bash
# Pull Requests
gh pr create --title "feat: add auth" --body "Description"
gh pr list --state open
gh pr view 42
gh pr merge 42 --squash --delete-branch
gh pr checks 42
gh pr review 42 --approve

# Issues
gh issue create --title "Bug: login fails" --body "Steps to reproduce..."
gh issue list --label bug --state open
gh issue close 42 --reason completed

# Runs (CI/CD)
gh run list --limit 5
gh run view 12345
gh run watch 12345
gh run rerun 12345 --failed

# Repository
gh repo view --json name,defaultBranchRef
gh api repos/{owner}/{repo}/branches/main/protection
```

### JSON Output for Scripting

```bash
gh pr list --json number,title,author,reviewDecision --jq '.[] | select(.reviewDecision == "APPROVED")'
gh issue list --json number,title,labels --jq '.[] | select(.labels | map(.name) | index("bug"))'
```

### CI Debugging Sequence

When CI fails:
1. `gh pr checks <number>` -- identify which check failed
2. `gh run view <run-id> --log-failed` -- read the failure logs
3. Fix locally, push, and verify with `gh run watch`

## GitHub Actions Basics

### Workflow Triggers

| Trigger | Use Case |
|---------|----------|
| `push` | Run on every push to specific branches |
| `pull_request` | Run on PR events (opened, synchronize, reopened) |
| `schedule` | Cron-based recurring jobs |
| `workflow_dispatch` | Manual trigger with optional inputs |
| `release` | Run on release creation |

### Key Practices

- Pin action versions to full SHA, not just major version
- Use `concurrency` to cancel superseded workflow runs on the same branch
- Cache dependencies (Maven, npm, pip) to speed up builds
- Use matrix builds for multi-version testing
- Store secrets in GitHub Secrets, never in workflow files
- Use `GITHUB_TOKEN` permissions at the minimum required level

### Reusable Workflows

```yaml
# .github/workflows/reusable-test.yml
name: Reusable Test
on:
  workflow_call:
    inputs:
      java-version:
        required: true
        type: string

jobs:
  test:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4
      - uses: actions/setup-java@v4
        with:
          java-version: ${{ inputs.java-version }}
          distribution: temurin
      - run: ./mvnw verify
```

## Issue Management

### Issue Templates

Use issue templates (`.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/`) to enforce structure:
- Bug reports: reproduction steps, expected vs actual, environment
- Feature requests: problem, proposed solution, alternatives
- Tasks: acceptance criteria, dependencies

### Labels

Maintain a consistent label taxonomy:

| Category | Labels |
|----------|--------|
| Type | `bug`, `feature`, `enhancement`, `docs`, `chore` |
| Priority | `P0-critical`, `P1-high`, `P2-medium`, `P3-low` |
| Status | `needs-triage`, `in-progress`, `blocked`, `ready-for-review` |
| Area | `api`, `auth`, `database`, `frontend`, `infra` |

## Branch Protection via API

```bash
gh api repos/{owner}/{repo}/branches/main/protection \
  --method PUT \
  --field required_status_checks='{"strict":true,"contexts":["build","test"]}' \
  --field enforce_admins=true \
  --field required_pull_request_reviews='{"required_approving_review_count":1}' \
  --field restrictions=null
```

## CODEOWNERS

Place `.github/CODEOWNERS` to auto-assign reviewers:

```
# Default owner for everything
* @team-lead

# Specific paths
/src/auth/     @security-team
/docs/         @docs-team
/infra/        @platform-team
*.sql          @dba-team
```
